quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,64,"Or He Who initiates the creation, then will create it again, and He Who provides you sustenance from the skies and the earth? Is there a God along with Allah?! Proclaim, “Bring your proof, if you are truthful!”"
  27,65,"Say (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), “None in the heavens and the earth know the hidden by themselves, except Allah; and they do not know when they will be raised.”"
  27,66,"Has their knowledge advanced so much as to know the Hereafter? On the contrary, they are in doubt concerning it; in fact they are blind towards it."
  27,67,"And the disbelievers said, “Will we, when we and our forefathers have turned into dust, be removed again?”"
  27,68,"“Indeed this promise was given to us, and before us to our forefathers – this is nothing but stories of former people.”"
  27,69,"“Proclaim, (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), “Travel in the land and see what sort of fate befell the guilty.”"
  27,70,"And do not grieve upon them, nor be distressed because of their scheming."
  27,71,"And they say, “When will this promise come, if you are truthful?”"
  27,72,"Say, “It could be that a part of what you are impatient for is (already) after you.”"
  27,73,"Indeed your Lord is Most Munificent upon mankind, but most men do not give thanks."
  27,74,"And indeed your Lord knows what is hidden in their bosoms, and what they disclose."
  27,75,"And all the hidden secrets of the heavens and the earth are (written) in a clear Book. (The Preserved Tablet)"
  27,76,"Indeed this Qur’an narrates to the Descendants of Israel most of the matters in which they differ."
